<h4>Exposé</h4>
<div class='textile space-l'><p>Based on recent research in formal linguistics, this volume provides a thorough description of the whole system of Romanian Noun Phrases, understood in an extended sense, that is, in addition to nouns, pronouns and determiners, it examines all the adnominal phrases: genitive-marked DPs, adjectives, relative clauses, appositions, prepositional phrases, complement clauses and non-finite modifiers. The book focuses on syntax and the syntax-semantics interface but also includes a systematic morphological description of the language. The implicitly comparative description of Romanian contained in the book can serve as a starting point for the study of the syntax/semantics of Noun Phrases in other languages, regardless of whether or not they are typologically related to Romanian. This book will be of special interest to linguists working on Romanian, Romance languages, comparative linguistics and language typology, especially because Romanian is relevant for comparative linguistics not only as a Romance language, but also as part of the so-called Balkan <em>Sprachbund</em>.</p></div>
<h4>Inhalt</h4>
<div class='textile'><p>Preface</p>
<p>Introduction: Nominal features and nominal projections<br />
Carmen Dobrovie-Sorin, Ion Giurgea and Donka F. Farkas</p>
<p>Bare nouns<br />
Carmen Dobrovie-Sorin</p>
<p>The syntax of determiners and other functional categories<br />
Ion Giurgea</p>
<p>The semantics of determiners<br />
Donka F. Farkas</p>
<p>Pronouns<br />
Sanda Reinheimer-Ripeanu, Liliane Tasmowski, Andra Vasilescu, Ion Giurgea, Andra Vasilescu and Rodica Zafiu</p>
<p>Genitive DPs and pronominal possessors<br />
Carmen Dobrovie-Sorin, Carmen Dobrovie-Sorin, Isabela Nedelcu, Carmen Dobrovie-Sorin and Ion Giurgea</p>
<p>The adjective<br />
Alexandra Cornilescu, Ion Giurgea and Ion Giurgea</p>
<p>Adnominal prepositional phrases<br />
Alexandru Mardale, Carmen Dobrovie-Sorin, Ion Giurgea, Alexandru Mardale, Ion Giurgea and Alexandru Mardale</p>
<p>Adnominal non-finite constituents and complement clauses<br />
Elena Negoiţă Soare, Rodica Zafiu and Elena Negoiţă Soare</p>
<p>Relative Clause Constructions and unbounded dependencies<br />
Alexander Grosu</p>
<p>Deverbal nouns<br />
Alexandra Cornilescu, Alexandra Cornilescu, Carmen Dobrovie-Sorin, Ion Giurgea, Alexandra Cornilescu, Elena Negoiţă Soare, Carmen Dobrovie-Sorin, Ion Giurgea, Camelia Stan and Ion Giurgea</p>
<p>Proper names<br />
Mihaela Miron-Fulea, Carmen Dobrovie-Sorin and Ion Giurgea</p>
<p>Classifier and qualitative binominal constructions<br />
Mihaela Tănase-Dogaru, Ion Giurgea, Mihaela Tănase-Dogaru, Ion Giurgea and Ruxandra Vişan</p>
<p>Appositions and juxtaposed nouns<br />
Raluca Brăescu and Ion Giurgea</p>
<p>Vocatives<br />
Blanca Croitor and Virginia Hill</p>
<p>Nominal inflection<br />
Ion Giurgea</p>
<p>Bibliography</p></div>
